Alarm rings in the timezone when it is set, not what the currently configured timezone is

note.body:
Of course you need to adhere to the timezone of an event.

The question to answer here is:
* "What is the timezone of an alarm clock?"

The answer to that is probably always:
* "Current local timezone"

Now, one *could* add UI that permits defining the timezone of the alarm clock. However, if there is no UI to choose the timezone, then "current local time" is the only sensible definition. And "local time" is subject to change at any point and that needs to be taken into consideration.
